@notice Perp-like leverage function
 @dev    Will revert if unable to satisfy totalCollateral. Depending on the
         current liquidity profile of the pool, certain amounts of leverage will
         be impossible to achieve.

@notice Repay an active credit position with reserves in exchange for bTokensIn
         collateral.
 @dev    Collateral returned is proportional to incoming reserves relative to
         total credit position (principal and interest).

@notice Extends the expiry of a user's credit account by taking in reserves
          and paying interest directly.
  @dev this will always transfer in reserves regardless of if there is credit available or not

@notice Estimates credit available for borrowing given user's previous
         collateral, new collateral and additional days
 @dev    This will charge an additional 2% interest on principal if
         trading in the floor.

@notice Calculates interest for a given amount of credit and number of days
 @dev    Interest math with full 18 decimals leads to precision issues with more
         days added. We instead scale down to 1e9 to avoid this.
